<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1660,2011]" box="[151,373,1660,1686]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<heading box="[151,373,1660,1686]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="5">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[151,373,1660,1686]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[151,373,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Holochilus sciureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1660,2011]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Karyotype: 2n = 56 and FN = 56. Autosomal complement: one small metacentric pair, and 26 acrocentric pairs large to small decreasing in size. Sex chromosomes: X, a medium acrocentric; Y, a small acrocentric (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vidal, O. R. &amp; Riva, R. &amp; Baro, N. I." box="[298,483,1768,1795]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="75 - 85" refId="ref74728" refString="Vidal, O. R., Riva, R. &amp; Baro, N. I. (1976) Los cromosomas del genero Holochilus. I. Polimorfismo en H. chacarius Thomas (1906). Physis, 35, 75 - 85." type="journal article" year="1976">
Vidal 
<emphasis box="[364,412,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 1976
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Patton, J. L. &amp; Silva, M. N. &amp; Malcolm, J. R." box="[494,693,1768,1795]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 306" refId="ref71077" refString="Patton, J. L., Silva, M. N. &amp; Malcolm, J. R. (2000) Mammals of the Rio Jurua and the evolutionary and ecological diversification of Amazonia. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 244, 1 - 306. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 244 % 3 C 0001: MOTRJA % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">
Patton 
<emphasis box="[571,619,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
).A fundamental number of 55 was reported due to a heteromorphic centric fusion (
<bibRefCitation author="Freitas, T. R. O. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Souza, M. J. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Salzano, F. M." box="[318,524,1804,1831]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="13 - 20" refId="ref66921" refString="Freitas, T. R. O., Mattevi, M. S., Oliveira, L. F. B., Souza, M. J., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Salzano, F. M. (1983) Chromosome relationships in three representatives of the genus Holochilus (Rodentia, Cricetidae) from Brazil. Genetica, 61, 13 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00563228" type="journal article" year="1983">
Freitas 
<emphasis box="[403,452,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 1983
</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 17, 
<figureCitation box="[618,685,1804,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1625,1649]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,712,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-177@23.[151,1436,705,1602]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Hylaeamys. (□) H. megacephalus; (■) H. oniscus; (○) H. perenensis; (l) H. seuanezi; (ê) H. yunganus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423629/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). A different morphology of sex chromosomes was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A." pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="209 - 220" refId="ref76205" refString="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y., Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A. (1987) Supernumerary chromosomes in Holochilus brasiliensis and comparative cytogenetic analysis with Nectomys squamipes (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Revista Brasileira de Genetica, 2, 209 - 220." type="journal article" year="1987">
Yonenaga-Yassuda 
<emphasis box="[339,389,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. (1987)
</bibRefCitation>
, a subtelocentric X and a submetacentric Y. These authors also reported the presence of one or two large submetacentric B chromosomes. C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of all autosomes. The X chromosome presented constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region and on the short arm, while the Y chromosome was completely heterochromatic. The B chromosomes presented heterochromatic blocks on the pericentromeric region and on both arms (
<bibRefCitation author="Freitas, T. R. O. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Souza, M. J. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Salzano, F. M." lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="13 - 20" refId="ref66921" refString="Freitas, T. R. O., Mattevi, M. S., Oliveira, L. F. B., Souza, M. J., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Salzano, F. M. (1983) Chromosome relationships in three representatives of the genus Holochilus (Rodentia, Cricetidae) from Brazil. Genetica, 61, 13 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00563228" type="journal article" year="1983">
Freitas 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 1983
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A." box="[258,603,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="209 - 220" refId="ref76205" refString="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y., Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A. (1987) Supernumerary chromosomes in Holochilus brasiliensis and comparative cytogenetic analysis with Nectomys squamipes (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Revista Brasileira de Genetica, 2, 209 - 220." type="journal article" year="1987">
Yonenaga-Yassuda 
<emphasis box="[478,528,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 1987
</bibRefCitation>
). G- and R-banding were also performed (
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, R. J. &amp; Koop, B. F. &amp; Haiduk, M. W." box="[1082,1283,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="403 - 416" refId="ref64229" refString="Baker, R. J., Koop, B. F. &amp; Haiduk, M. W. (1983) Resolving systematic relationships with G-bands: a study of five genera of South American Cricetine rodents. Systematic zoology, 32 (4), 403 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2413167" type="journal article" year="1983">
Baker 
<emphasis box="[1159,1209,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 1983
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Freitas, T. R. O. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Souza, M. J. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Salzano, F. M." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="13 - 20" refId="ref66921" refString="Freitas, T. R. O., Mattevi, M. S., Oliveira, L. F. B., Souza, M. J., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Salzano, F. M. (1983) Chromosome relationships in three representatives of the genus Holochilus (Rodentia, Cricetidae) from Brazil. Genetica, 61, 13 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00563228" type="journal article" year="1983">
Freitas 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 1983
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A." box="[221,563,187,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="209 - 220" refId="ref76205" refString="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y., Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A. (1987) Supernumerary chromosomes in Holochilus brasiliensis and comparative cytogenetic analysis with Nectomys squamipes (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Revista Brasileira de Genetica, 2, 209 - 220." type="journal article" year="1987">
Yonenaga-Yassuda 
<emphasis box="[440,489,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 1987
</bibRefCitation>
). Multiple NORs, varying from six to fourteen were localized at the telomeric regions of the short arms of small autosomes (
<bibRefCitation author="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A." box="[667,1011,223,249]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="209 - 220" refId="ref76205" refString="Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y., Prado, R. C. &amp; Mello, D. A. (1987) Supernumerary chromosomes in Holochilus brasiliensis and comparative cytogenetic analysis with Nectomys squamipes (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Revista Brasileira de Genetica, 2, 209 - 220." type="journal article" year="1987">
Yonenaga-Yassuda 
<emphasis box="[888,937,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 1987
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Supernumerary chromosomes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[579,708,259,284]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[579,708,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. sciureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were isolated by flow-sorted and used as probe for understand the origin of B chromosomes in tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[573,712,295,321]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Oryzomyini">Oryzomyini</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis box="[723,793,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">In situ</emphasis>
hybridization of Bs and sex chromosomes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1310,1436,295,320]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. sciureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were performed on metaphases of 15 species of 
<taxonomicName box="[708,846,331,357]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Oryzomyini">Oryzomyini</taxonomicName>
, five of which had Bs. The results revealed that 12 of the species sampled, all belonging to a monophyletic 
<taxonomicName box="[788,923,367,393]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Oryzomyini">Oryzomyini</taxonomicName>
subclade (clade C and D, recovered by Weksler 2006), were positive for an anonymous ‘Oryzomyini’ shared heterochromatic region (OSHR) on the X and Y chromosomes. The OSHR was also present on Bs of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[742,867,439,464]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[742,867,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. sciureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[881,1062,439,464]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Nectomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rattus">
<emphasis box="[881,1062,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Nectomys rattus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brants" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[1123,1273,439,464]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Nectomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamipes">
<emphasis box="[1123,1273,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">N. squamipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not on Bs of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[182,461,475,501]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis box="[182,461,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Oligoryzomys flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[524,758,475,501]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Sooretamys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angouya">
<emphasis box="[524,758,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Sooretamys angouya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two distinct additional OSHR/autosome associations were observed on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[294,418,511,537]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Sooretamys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angouya">
<emphasis box="[294,418,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">S. angouya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to the authors, the OSHR possibly arose 3.0 to 7.8 million years ago on the sex chromosomes of an ancestral species and spread through the action of transposable elements. These results suggest that the diversity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bs" authorityName="Bs" box="[384,558,583,609]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Oryzomyini">Oryzomyini Bs</taxonomicName>
in number, size, morphology, and genetic content may be explained by their independent origin in different subgroups of species (Ventura 
<emphasis box="[844,893,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
